deck: Archibald Morton was the second Chemistro and an enemy of Power Man.
description:
Origin

Archibald Morton discovered the power of Alchemy Gun while in prison. There he beat another inmate named Curtis Carr, whom was the supervillain known as Chemistro and was arrested after a battle with Luke Cage, Power Man. Arch forced Curtis to tell him how to build the alchemy gun. Finally, Curtis gave in and told him his secret. When Arch came out of prison, he immediately started building the weapon. However, he wasn't careful and Curtis had left out some of the details. The gun exploded and chemical properties of the gun spilled all over him. This freak accident made it that now, Arch was able to transform matter without his gun, merely with his mind and hands, making him a formidable foe.

Creation

Arch Morton, the second Chemistro, first appeared in Power Man #37.

Character Evolution

Luke Cage however, noticing the similarities between Arch and Curtis, called upon the help of Curtis Carr. Carr, who had fell into a depression after he was let out of prison, realized that it was his duty to stop Arch. Carr made the Nullifier to cancel out Arch's powers. So thanks to Carr's brilliance, Cage defeated and de-powered the second Chemistro.

Origin

Dr. Mays's mother.

Creation

Written by Max Bemis and drawn by Jorge Coelho.

Seemingly losing her mind, Mrs. Mays stays in her room and draws cryptic symbols on the wall. When the child Dr. Mays approaches her about some food she turns on him and threatens him with a knife. deck: Mako was only a young child when a Kaiju attack on Tokyo claimed the lives of her entire family. She was saved by a young Stacker Pentecost, who adopted her and raised her as his own. When she grew up, she joined the Jaeger program  and became Gipsy Danger's co-pilot.
description:
In the year 2016, a Category II Kaiju codenamed "Onibaba" attacked Tokyo and killed thousands of civilians. A young Mako watched as her entire family disappeared in the blink of an eye. The Kaiju pursued her down the deserted streets of the city until Coyote Tango, a Jaeger captained by Stacker Pentecost and Tamsin Sevier, arrived on the scene and slew the monster in a brutal battle. In the aftermath of the creature's defeat, Stacker found Mako and adopted her as his own daughter, since she had no family left and no one to look after her.

Other Media

Pacific Rim (2013)

An adult Mako who is a candidate for the Jaeger program appears in Guillermo del Toro's Pacific Rim film. She is played by Rinko Kikuchi, and in flashback childhood scenes by Mana Ashida. During the final assault on the Breach between Earth and the Kaiju universe, she is Raleigh Becket's co-pilot onboard the Gipsy Danger.

Origin

deck: Indra Ohtsutsuki is the eldest son of the Sage of Six Paths. He believed that power was the way to peace. His line would go on to become the Uchiha Clan.
description:
Origin

Indra was the first born of Hagoromo's sons. He was gifted with Hagoromo's eyes and spiritual energy, and from birth was a prodigy. He was exceptional and he was all too aware of his superiority, doing everything on his own and feeling that anything could be achieved with might. This didn't bode well for Hagoromo, whom when deciding on which of his sons would succeed him before he died, chose his younger son instead. Indra believed it was his birthright and, upon Black Zetsu's manipulation and goading, fought Ashura for the honor, resulting in their mutual deaths.

He was reincarnated numerous times over the millenium, his most recent reincarnations being Madara and then Sasuke.
